added.title: Intro
added.description: Control Freak leads the Titans on a chase through various cartoon intro sequences.

added.title: Haunted Tank
added.description: At a Halloween festival, the Titans meet the famous Haunted Tank and its ghostly inhabitant, General Tucker.

added.title: Warner Bros 100TH Anniversary
added.description: The Titans are in charge of the 100th Anniversary party for Warner Bros on the studio lot and everything is going well until the magical WB Shield is broken into pieces.

added.title: Wishbone
added.description: The Titans make wishes on a wishbone, but when it's broken, they must travel to Gobble-Gobble Land to set things right.

added.title: Ship
added.description: Starfire is the captain of a spaceship heading back to her home planet of Tarmaran and her crew is some of Earth's finest specimens.

added.title: Catpin Freak
added.description: Seeing the benefits of being captain, Freak demands the position which worries the rest of the crew.

added.title: 50% Crew
added.description: A teleportation malfunction causes the spaceship crew to lose their upper halves.

added.title: Wild Card
added.description: Starfire and her crew go on a dangerous mission to prevent Blackfire from acquiring a powerful Tamaranean relic.

added.title: Five Bucks
added.description: Starfire and her crew play Tooth Fairy for the Tooth Fairy.

added.title: The Streak Part 1
added.description: It's Crime Season and Robin is determined to continue his streak of stopping 52 crimes every year.

added.title: I'm the Sauce
added.description: Stuck inside because of bad weather, the Titans play rainy day games after Robin convinces them that indoor activities will cheer up the clouds and make the rain stop.

added.title: Grandma Voice
added.description: In order to defeat Mother Mae Eye, Cyborg starts using a grandma voice but soon that persona takes over and he begins making the other Titans dress warmly and clean their dishes.

added.title: The Brain
added.description: Anais has been facepalming every time her family does something stupid, which has led to a serious medical condition. In fact, if she facepalms just one more time she could do her brain irreparable damage, so the Wattersons have to get through the week without doing anything idiotic.

added.title: The Founder
added.description: When Nicole decides to pay the cable bill in person at Chanax, she leaves specific instructions for Richard to stay in the car. However he's far too tempted by the vending machine in the foyer to follow her advice. Chanax believes Richard is their mysterious founder and follow his every whim, leading to their inevitable demise.

added.title: The Future
added.description: Gumball, Darwin and Banana Joe investigate Banana Barbara's mysterious disappearance and uncover an old rival's shadowy scheme in the process.

added.title: The Wish
added.description: Gumball and Darwin panic when they suspect they've accidentally turned Miss Simian into a cushion, by wishing upon an enchanted key ring. Surely the only way to break the curse is a confession of true love from Principal Brown. Simple!

added.title: The Factory
added.description: Gumball and Darwin follow Nicole to the Rainbow Factory for Bring your Kids to Work Day. They are expecting a magical place full of dreams and wonder but it turns out to be a little less magical than they'd hoped. Despite the fact nobody wants them there, they end up saving the factory from being closed down.

added.title: The Agent
added.description: Gumball and Darwin's clothes go missing after a swimming lesson and Gumball is forced to wear a tuxedo from the lost and found office. He believes it makes him look like a certain dapper British secret agent and, together with Darwin and Bobert (and far too many wisecracks) Gumball track down the villain responsible for stealing his clothes.

added.title: The Web
added.description: Gumball and Darwin realize that the adult residents of Elmore are dangerously naive when it comes to being safe online. In fact they are in serious need of the boys help with even the simplest of tasks. And no more so than their mom, Nicole.

added.title: The Mess
added.description: The boys stay up all night, even though the next day they're supposed to be babysitting Polly, Penny's little sister. They're so tired that they manage to lose Polly in the blink of an eye. They desperately look for her, but find themselves in increasingly weird situations every time they accidentally nod off.

added.title: The Heart
added.description: When Mr. Robinson accidentally let slip how little he cares for Gumball and Darwin, they react by giving him the cold shoulder.  Surprisingly Mr. Robinson misses them and tries to win back their friendship. After a few failed attempts, Gumball and Darwin realize that Mr. Robinson's heart is protecting him, so they give it an intense affection overload.

added.title: The Revolt
added.description: Darwin tries to highlight the plight of all the household objects he feels are being oppressed and maltreated by the uncaring residents of Elmore. He then decides to lead those objects in a revolt against the townspeople.

added.title: The Decisions
added.description: When everything goes wrong in Darwin's life, he begins to suspect that Gumball's bad influence might be to blame. Darwin decides to go elsewhere for guidance and finds a new mentor in Alan. But maybe it's time Darwin started making his own decisions.

added.title: The BFFS
added.description: Gumball's old BFF Fuzzy, turns up on his doorstep. Darwin struggles to accept that there was someone before him and fails to contain his jealousy. But is Darwin right to mistrust Fuzzy? Does Fuzzy actually have sinister motives for reconnecting with his old BFF?

added.title: The Inquisition
added.description: The students of Elmore Junior High find their world turned upside down when the mysterious school superintendent comes to stamp out their cartoonish ways. But who wants to be normal? Certainly not Gumball and Darwin.

added.title: The Return
added.description: Dad is in charge of getting the kids to their first day back at school on time, but he's overslept and now he can't find Gumball, Darwin or Anais anywhere. He sets about retracing his steps from the day before to work out where they might be.

added.title: The Money
added.description: The Wattersons have run out of money and are torn between being broke and selling out. Richard has lost all of the family's money. Nicole is happy for the Wattersons to appear in a Joyful Burger commercial for some much needed cash. However Gumball protests as he is convinced it's selling out. He persuades the family to stick to their principles, but they find sticking to a tiny budget even harder.

added.title: Craig Before The Creek
added.description: Before he was Craig of the Creek, he was just Craig - a new kid in a new town. All Craig wants is to go back to his old friends at his old home. But when he learns that the nearby creek is hiding a lost treasure that could make his wish come true, Craig sets off on a journey to find it - navigating the perilous suburban wilderness, forging new friendships, all while being pursued by a fearsome band of pirates who are bent on destroying the Creek itself.

added.title: The Future is Cardboard
added.description: The kids meet an eccentric Cardboard Creator that invites Craig to help finish his masterpiece.

added.title: The Brood
added.description: Craig's determination to get his granddad a cicada shell causes him, Kelsey and JP to become trapped in their stump!

added.title: Whatever Happened to Babsy Bunny?
added.description: Babs is drawn into the world of modeling by animal calendar photographer, Elmyra Duff, while Plucky grapples with a bad caricature.

added.title: Slay Cheese
added.description: It's picture day at Acme Loo! Babs accidentally shrinks herself, Buster fails to get the perfect photo day haircut, Plucky gives lessons on being direct, and Hamton struggles to find his photo persona.

added.title: Tooned In Space
added.description: The toons take Marvin the Martian's class, and head to space. Buster tries to cheer up a homesick Babs, Plucky searches for a space outfit, and Sweetie is too obsessed with a video game to notice any of it - even when the aliens attack!

added.title: Twin-Con
added.description: Babs and Buster attend a twin convention but are soon ostracized for not being exactly the same. Hamton accidentally becomes famous, and Plucky steps up as his manager. And Sweetie won't let anything stop her from finishing her board game.

added.title: Freshman Orientoontion
added.description: It's the first day of school at Acme Looniversity - the Harvard of being stupid - where we find fraternal twins, Babs and Buster Bunny meeting their new friends - tough chick Sweetie Bird, self-effacing sweetheart Hamton J. Pig, and narcissist clown, Plucky Duck. These young dreamers all share the same big plans - to learn how to be  professional toons -  and their journey begins now.

added.title: Give Pizza a Chance
added.description: Rivals Buster and Plucky decide to throw an epic pizza party and are shocked to find out they're actually getting along while Babs and Sweetie get into their first roommate disagreement.

added.title: Extra, So Extra
added.description: Babs realizes Acme Loo's school paper has closed so she starts a new one with her pal Sweetie. But when Plucky starts a gossipy tabloid to compete against them, which paper will come out on top?

added.title: Tooney Ball Lights
added.description: Buster and Sweetie join the Tooney Ball team during Electives Week while Babs and Plucky tackle the basics in Anvils 101, leaving Hamton on a journey to fix his indecisiveness.

added.title: Save The Loo Bru
added.description: Buster meets his nemesis, Montana Max, and must apply a new lesson from Bugs about drag to keep the Loo Bru from demolition.

added.title: Prank You Very Much
added.description: It's Prank Week at Acme Loo and our pals get into escalating shenanigans trying to out prank their rival, Aqua Loo.

added.title: General HOGspital
added.description: Hamton gets into medical school but soon realizes it's not at all what he imagined. Buster desperately tries to find a way to bring his pal back to Acme Loo.

added.title: Soufflé, Girl Hey
added.description: Babs and Buster are excited to get college jobs, but can they stand the heat cooking for the school chef?

added.title: Tears Of A Clone
added.description: Buster finds a cloning machine at Wile E. Coyote's yard sale that he uses to make another Buster and Babs and Sweetie snag a time machine that they use to open a vintage clothing store.

added.title: The Show Must Hop On
added.description: Babs is excited to be the first student director of the annual toon showcase, but she quickly learns it won't be as easy as she thought. Meanwhile, with the help of his friends, Hamton learns to shine in the spotlight.

added.title: Spring Beak
added.description: Plucky goes home with Babs and Buster for Spring Break and quickly becomes the new star of Burrowville, while Hamton and Sweetie embark on the adventure after accidently missing their train stop.

added.title: The Prince and the Legendary Rabbit Hood
added.description: Mistaking Prince Ivandoe for a lowly peasant, Rabbit Hood bestows upon him precious jewelry - that she has stolen from a Prince. Prince Svan to be precise! Who is none too pleased to discover his precious items in Ivandoe's possession! Ivandoe and Bert evade capture and set off on a quest to find Rabbit Hood. They must persuade her to return Svan's treasures, thereby clearing Ivandoe's princely name.
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Yucky Duckling
added.description: A Hooded Stranger from Prince Ivandoe's past seeks revenge by attempting to ruin Ivandoe's perfect princely appearance. Bert repeatedly foils his attempts, so the Hooded Stranger kidnaps Bert and whisks him off to his lair. Time for Prince Ivandoe to rescue Bert and discover just what he did to anger the Hooded Stranger in the first place!
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Unruly Royal
added.description: Prince Ivandoe receives instructions from his father, The Mighty Stag. He is to escort his spoilt cousin Dudley to a correctional school, ran by Posy Pippins - the strictest and most feared Governess in the land! However, along the way, much to Bert's dismay, Ivandoe falls under the influence of the unruly Dudley and starts to misbehave. So much so that when they arrive at Posy Pippins' Unruly School, she decides to keep both Dudley and Ivandoe! Bert attempts to rescue Prince Ivandoe by posing as an even stricter Governor.
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Show-Off Stallion
added.description: When the legendary Mighty Stallion "out-hero's" Prince Ivandoe by saving the Bunny Village from a terrifying beastie, Ivandoe loses his confidence. Even though the Stallion demands payments in carrots, which is in direct violation of the Hero Code, Ivandoe feels he cannot compete with such a magnificent fellow. Bert must help his master find his mojo again, before the Bunny Village is destroyed by an even bigger terrifying beastie!
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Dark Lord of Moletown
added.description: Prince Ivandoe is unsurprised to discover that he is worshipped by a group of moles. Their leader, the sinister Dark Lord of Moletown, is convinced that Ivandoe's magic potion once bestowed upon him the ability to see in the daylight. The Dark Lord now wishes for Ivandoe to use his magic on his moley minions, so that they might rise up as an unstoppable army and take over the forest! When the moles realize Ivandoe isn't actually magic, things go a little "squiggly".
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Feast of the Fopdoodles
added.description: Prince Ivandoe reluctantly accepts an invitation to a Royal MidSwanner Feast. "Reluctantly" because the invitation is from his nemesis, the awful Prince Svan of Svanland! As the feast progresses, it becomes increasingly clear that Prince Ivandoe, along with three rather peculiar guests, are the unwitting victims of a typically cruel Swan deception. Swans!!!!!!
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Boasty Boar
added.description: In an attempt to win the hand of Princess Jezabel, Boaris Von Tusk stages a tournament to prove that he is the greatest warrior in all The Five Kingdoms. Prince Ivandoe takes part, of course, for no warrior is greater than he! But so too does a Masked Knight who not only wins but turns out to be... Jezebel herself! For Jezebel is nobody's prize!!!
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Blobby Princess
added.description: Princess Syllabob, the blobby daughter of Axalotly, King of the Deep, has been carried off by a gang of gulls and discarded on the forest floor. Prince Ivandoe and Bert happen upon her and agree to escort the Princess back to the lake before she dehydrates. Overcoming obstacles, including a swan-napping by Prince Svan, Ivandoe and Syllabob develop... well, a sort of... friendship?
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Wise Wizard of Wisdom
added.description: Struck down by a poisonous turnip, Prince Ivandoe & Bert must seek a cure from the Wise Wizard of Wisdom. They set off, and along the way, they are joined by an equally desperate small-faced bear, a bunny-dragon, and a truly useless fairy. Once they reach the Wise Wizard however, they discover that he is a lot less wise and a lot more "sassy" than anyone could have predicted!
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Squeak of Obedience
added.description: Feral and her gang of cat-thieves have stolen Prince Ivandoe's map to Eagle Mountain. Cupcake, the pink-poodle survivalist offers to train Prince Ivandoe to become a Jungle Warrior. So that together they can infiltrate Feral's camp and get back whats theirs. For Feral also stole a precious item from Cupcake... one that exerts a strange hold over him - "The Squeak of Obedience!"
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Princenappers
added.description: Whilst travelling through the notoriously dangerous Forest of Outlaws, Prince Ivandoe is repeatedly Princenapped! First by a gang of wolves in disguise, then by Boaris and his Merry Boars, and finally by Feral and her gang of cat-thieves - all of them hoping to secure a royal ransom. Luckily for Prince Ivandoe and Bert, they are rescued by the fair Jezabel - though, as it turns out, not with the noblest of intentions.
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Playdate
added.description: Prince Ivandoe is a prisoner in the castle dungeon of Jezabel's mother, Grizabella - the unpredictable and slightly terrifying "Queen of Thieves". Whilst waiting for a royal random, Grizabella encourages her daughter to enjoy her "playdate" with the little prince. Prince Ivandoe is all too eager to do the same. However, when Grizabella demands that Prince Ivandoe perform as her Royal Jester - Ivandoe and Bert realise they need to escape. At once!!
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Valiant Quest
added.description: Prince Ivandoe and Bert set off on their heroic quest and, almost immediately, a winged serpent steals their map to Eagle Mountain. But that shan't stop a plucky young buck and his devoted squire from fulfilling their destiny. With the assistance of a quite staggeringly incompetent Dwarf called Alan, a new sword is forged and the Quest continue-eth!
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Chicken of Doom
added.description: A fire-breathing Giant Chicken is destroying the local farmers' prize vegetables. Prince Ivandoe vows to capture the Giant Chicken, but... gets captured by her instead. He seems to bring out her maternal side, and she in turn reminds him of Nanny. So when an angry mob attacks, Ivandoe heroically jumps to his Giant Nanny-Chicken's defence.
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Sing-Songy Stag
added.description: When Prince Ivandoe valiantly sets free Brian the Bard, he discovers he is now stuck with him... until such time that Brian saves Prince Ivandoe's life in return. This would not be so awful if Brian didn't send all day singing accurate, yet deeply unflattering, songs about Prince Ivandoe's looks and abilities.
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Tears of Triumph
added.description: In an effort to impress Jezebel the thiefstress, Prince Ivandoe and Bert set off to find the elusive Centicore. For the Magic Tears of the Centicore are rumored to cure all known ailments. But how exactly does one make a massive mountain-goat, made from stone, blub?
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Turnip Tricksters
added.description: Prince Ivandoe vows to capture the turnip thief... the very worst type of thief! Prince Ivandoe and Bert are guided by some suspiciously Germanic woodland characters towards an old cabin. It turns out to be an elaborate trap, devised by the Sassy Gnomes, to punish Ivandoe for his inconsiderate turnip-top littering.
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Swoony Swanstress
added.description: Prince Ivandoe and Bert take a lovely, but lost and confused, Swanstress under their wing. When finally, her memory returns, it turns out she is none other than the awful Princess Svandelyne, stuck-up sister to Prince Svan - Prince Ivandoe's greatest nemesis! And when Svan turns up, well, this can only end up in a Prince-Off. And does!
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Feather Fluffer-Upper
added.description: Prince Ivandoe and Bert reluctantly agree to bring Princess Syllabob of the Underwater Kingdom an all-powerful Trident for her Sweet Sixteenth birthday. However, it is currently in the possession of Ivandoe's great nemesis - Prince Svan - who has found another, less dignified, use for it. Ivandoe and Bert must risk all, entering the Swan Palace and avoiding the appalling Royal Family, in order to fulfill their promise to King Axalotyl, King of the Deep.
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Talking Tree
added.description: Ivandoe and Bert come across a Talking Tree who promises to tell their fortune in exchange for gold. An enthusiastic Ivandoe hands over his golden locket, just before Bert discovers the sassy gnomes hidden away inside the hollow tree! Let battle commence…again!
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Hissy Swan
added.description: Ivandoe comes face to face with a cocky young swan prince.  To settle their differences they engage in a good old-fashioned Prince-Off with the help of their trusty squires.  Ivandoe's underwhelming royal roar unexpectedly saves the day.
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Raspberry Fairy
added.description: While escaping from a grizzly bear, Ivandoe and Bert fall into an underground cave where a large Troll-woman in a party dress keeps them captive in order to  play with them like dolls.
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Pretty Poodle
added.description: Ivandoe and Bert get captured and tied up by a very intense forest survivalist who happens to be …. a pink poodle. Bert figures out a way to escape using the poodle's canine instincts…
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Plucky Duck
added.description: Ivandoe dismisses Bert and takes on a duck as his new Squire. The duck proves to be worse than useless when they come face to face with an angry tentacled forest creature. Ivandoe misses Bert and wants him back but is too proud to admit it…
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Prom-Date
added.description: A formidable king of the deep drags Ivandoe and Bert to the bottom of his lake, so that Ivandoe can be a royal prom-date for his daughter, the devastatingly unattractive Princess Syllabob.
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Moany Mountain
added.description: Ivandoe and Bert must remove an annoying creature from the "nose" of a magical mountain in order to continue on their quest. They almost come to a very sticky end…
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Sassy Gnomes
added.description: A bunch of sassy gnomes refuse to allow Ivandoe to cross their shiny bridge on his quest for The Golden Feather. When they combine to become one huge fighting gnome, Bert accidentally saves the day.
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Kissy Frog
added.description: Ivandoe and Bert come across a tiny miserable prince in the forest.  He needs a kiss to transform him back into the beautiful bullfrog he once was.  But Ivandoe and Bert are not into kissing.  They're into questing.  Quest on!!!
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Thieftress
added.description: Ivandoe and Bert comes to the rescue when a damsel in distress is being threatened by a big scary wolf. Will the enchanting young lady steal more than Ivandoe's heart?
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: Unica's House
added.description: The bears learn about sleepovers when visiting Unica in her hometown.

added.title: Rexford's Nectar
added.description: In an effort to be a conscious consumer, Panda becomes obsessed with a new eco-friendly product.

added.title: Grizz's Doc
added.description: Unica and the bears enter into Glitterwood's annual bake off while Grizz documents it.

added.title: Triple T Tiger Lilies
added.description: It's time to grow the best flowers in Glitterwood forest! But Unica and the bears soon realize that they're all thumbs, and none of them are green! When the Triple T Tigers show off their awesome tiger lily, Unica and the bears decide it's time to do whatever it takes to grow their own awesome flower. But short cuts and bad decisions soon result in a disaster of gigantic proportion!

added.title: After Bedtime
added.description: Ice Bear sneaks away after hours to right a wrong.

added.title: The Parade
added.description: Unica is half donkey and half unicorn, and doesn't know which float to ride in the heritage parade. The bears volunteer to help her choose.

added.title: The Big Bloom
added.description: Unica and the bears prepare to rock out in order to help the Grand Magnolia Tree bloom.

added.title: A Very Special Special That's Quite Special
added.description: When Duncan destroys the school using an unsafe app Chef ends up with a big cash settlement, but rather than rebuilding the school, he takes the kids on a cross country adventure to a waterpark.

added.title: A New Life
added.description: Apple and Onion both leave their homes and follow their dreams to the big city but things don't go quite to plan.

added.title: The Perfect Team
added.description: Onion worries his relationship with Apple is in jeopardy when a stray cat enters the picture.

added.title: Tips
added.description: Apple and Onion have to find a way to ride the Hot Air Balloon which is in their town for one day only.

added.title: Falafel's Fun Day
added.description: When Falafel decides to pack up and leave the city, Apple and Onion have to convince him to stay or they'll have to leave too.

added.title: Apple's in Trouble
added.description: Apple is challenged to a fight by a grumpy Cheesesteak, so he and Onion go on a quest to find the source of Cheesesteak's grumpiness.

added.title: 4 on 1
added.description: Onion's fear of crowds threatens his basketball team's success.

added.title: Hotdog's Movie Premiere
added.description: Apple and Onion square off against a no-nonsense security guard after they're banned from the premiere of their friend Hot Dog's new movie.

added.title: Bottle Catch
added.description: Apple and Onion's favorite game attracts some unexpected attention.

added.title: Pancake's Bus Tour
added.description: Apple and Onion go on a guided bus tour as part of their plan to get Apple's shoe back.

added.title: Block Party
added.description: Apple and Onion have to outwit a mean duck who's taken over their building's roof.

added.title: Apple's Focus
added.description: Apple decides to help Onion achieve his dream of competing on a baking show.

added.title: Lil Noodle
added.description: Apple and Onion must remain legit enough to be in their favorite rapper's music video.

added.title: Gyranoid of the Future
added.description: Apple and Onion are dead set on riding Gyranoid of the Future, the craziest roller coaster at the carnival.

added.title: Fun Proof
added.description: Apple and Onion want to become this week's "Most Fun People".

added.title: Whale Spotting
added.description: In order to see a rare whale, Apple and Onion have to become members of an exclusive club, but one of them doesn't quite have the chops.

added.title: Our Stuff
added.description: After the bears play a little pickup basketball (they're very bad), they go back to grab their stuff by the side of the court only to find it's been stolen!  The Bears race across town trying to track down their stuff and end up cracking a giant case in the process.

added.title: Viral Video
added.description: The Bears think they have what it takes to make and star in a viral video, but when Nom-Nom decides that they don't, Grizz breaks into the koala's limo in an effort to change his mind.

added.title: Food Truck
added.description: The Bears open up a food truck after being disappointed by the food options available to them. In an effort to drum up business, they start selling their food to animals until the animals go a little crazy.

added.title: Chloe
added.description: Chloe spends time with the Bears in an effort to research them for an upcoming presentation. But when the Bears sneak a peek at her very dry report, the Bears decide to jazz it up with exaggerated facts about themselves and their lifestyle.

added.title: Panda's Date
added.description: When a vendor at the Farmer's Market (LUCY) sticks Panda with an EpiPen reviving him after an allergic reaction, Panda comes to in the arms of his dream girl. Panda tries to woo this woman of his dreams but his brothers and his own insecurities get in the way.

added.title: Everyday Bears
added.description: It's a normal day for the Bears. This means that Ice gets in a fight with a Roomba, Panda's life gets turned upside down when a mouse invades his room and Grizz gets stuck in a tree. You know, everyday stuff for a bear.

added.title: Burrito
added.description: Grizz likes Burritos. A lot. So much so that after a restaurant makes a Bear-Sized Burrito, Grizz can't bring himself to eat such a majestic work of art. He carries the burrito everywhere making it a new and increasingly smelly part of his life.

added.title: Primal
added.description: Have the Bears lost their survival instincts by living in the modern world? Grizz wants to know so he purposefully gets the Bears lost in the deep forest.

added.title: Jean Jacket
added.description: The Bears find a bedazzled jean jacket in a dumpster. It's just about the coolest thing they've ever seen and seems to make the wearer of the jacket extremely lucky. But after the Bears fight over who gets control of the jacket, they have to consider that their denim blessing has become a curse.

added.title: Nom Nom
added.description: When Nom Nom shows up on the Bears' doorstep, disheveled and deposed from his spot as cutest internet star ever after a recent meltdown, he enlists the Bears to help him regain his title.

added.title: Shush Ninjas
added.description: The Bears are fed up with the decay of etiquette at today's theaters. The Bears take it upon themselves to be the police of the theater, sneaking up like ninjas to shush people who ruin the movie for others with their bad manners.

added.title: My Clique
added.description: Chloe, a child prodigy, finds it difficult to connect with her much older classmates. The Bears take her under their wing and show her how to make great college friends.

added.title: Charlie
added.description: You know that one annoying friend who just can't get the hint? That's Charlie, and he's Bigfoot. The Bears meet him when Charlie signs up on a home-sharing website to spend a weekend with the Bears. Charlie is the worst possible house guest for the Bears and nearly destroys their house.

added.title: Brother Up
added.description: After Panda stumbles and accidentally scares a pack of wolves away in the process, the hierarchy of the Bears is disrupted. Suddenly, Panda has become the alpha bear, and he and Grizz have to deal with the consequences of an emotional Panda being the leader of the three Bears.

added.title: Occupy Bears
added.description: When the city plans to destroy the Bears' cave in order to make way for a new cell phone tower, Grizz and Panda must find evidence from their past that proves they have rights to their land. And in case that fails, Ice Bear protests and tries to sabotage the construction crew.

added.title: Your Mother and Mine
added.description: Steven takes Garnet to meet some of his new friends.

added.title: I Am My Mom
added.description: Steven struggles to fix his mistakes.

added.title: Say Uncle
added.description: A long lost relative of Steven's comes to town to aid him in unlocking the power of his mother's Gem!

added.title: Story for Steven
added.description: Greg tells Steven the full story of how he met Rose-Quartz.

added.title: Shirt Club
added.description: Steven and Buck Dewey make t-shirts together.

added.title: Love Letters
added.description: Steven and Connie help Jamie the mailman with love.

added.title: Reformed
added.description: Steven, Amethyst and Garnet chase after a monster that's been loose in the Temple.

added.title: Sworn to the Sword
added.description: Connie trains with Pearl to be a swordfighter.

added.title: Rising Tides, Crashing Skies
added.description: Ronaldo does some investigative reporting on whether Steven and the Crystal Gems are safe for Beach City.

added.title: Keeping It Together
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems revisit the Kindergarten and find a dark secret.

added.title: We Need to Talk
added.description: Greg tells Steven and Connie the story of how he learned about Gem fusion.

added.title: Chille Tid
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems try to relax with a slumber party.

added.title: Rose's Room
added.description: Steven's desire for some alone time unlocks a new room in the Temple that answers his every wish.

added.title: Lion 3: Straight to Video
added.description: Lion won't stop laying on Steven's face while he sleeps.

added.title: Rose's Scabbard
added.description: Steven joins Pearl on a special mission to a place that belonged to Rose-Quartz.

added.title: A Very Special Episode
added.description: Rainbow Quartz 2.0 promised to hang out with Onion the same day Sunstone scheduled a home safety Geminar! How can Steven be in two places, and two fusions, at once?

added.title: Snow Day
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems get a chance to catch up when they're all snowed in together.

added.title: Why So Blue?
added.description: Steven has heard rumors of a pair of Gems that are still destroying worlds. If he can't stop them, maybe Lapis can.

added.title: Little Graduation
added.description: Steven and the Gems celebrate Little Homeschool's first graduating class.

added.title: Prickly Pair
added.description: After leaving Little Homeschool, Steven has found a new hobby, plants.

added.title: Abstract
added.description: As Jake goes through some personal changes, he's haunted by a sinister dream encounter with his brother Jermaine.

added.title: Ketchup
added.description: BMO and Marceline swap stories about their recent adventures.

added.title: Islands Part 1: The Invitation
added.description: A mysterious craft invades Ooo and Finn believes it may hold the secrets to his past.

added.title: Islands Part 2: Whipple the Happy Dragon
added.description: Finn, Jake, and Susan set sail on a ocean voyage full of wonders and danger.

added.title: Islands Part 3: Mysterious Island
added.description: After waking up alone and shipwrecked, Finn investigates a bizarre island in search of his friends.

added.title: Islands Part 4: Imaginary Resources
added.description: Finn and Jake travel to a land where reality has been redesigned and improved.

added.title: Islands Part 5: Hide and Seek
added.description: While exploring some futuristic ruins, Susan sees glimpses of a familiar girl.

added.title: Islands Part 6: Min & Marty
added.description: An unexpected revelation from Susan leads Finn closer to answers about his past.

added.title: Islands Part 7: Helpers
added.description: Finn and his friends journey to a last refuge called Founders Island.

added.title: Islands Part 8: The Light Cloud
added.description: Finn confronts the power behind Founders Island, but will he ever return home to Ooo?

added.title: Finn the Human
added.description: After chasing the Lich through the portal, Finn and Jake meet a wishmaster named Prismo.

added.title: Jake the Dog
added.description: Jake and Prismo watch from the portal as the Ice King's crown makes Finn more and more powerful.

added.title: Conquest of Cuteness
added.description: King Snuggadoodle and the Huggaboopies invade Finn and Jake's tree house.

added.title: Memories of Boom Boom Mountain
added.description: Finn gets caught up in trying to make everyone happy.

added.title: Rainy Day Daydream
added.description: Jake's imagination runs wild and Finn has to stop it before it kills them.

added.title: Maxin' and Relaxin'
added.description: Mordecai wants to get a mix tape from his parents' house.

added.title: Brilliant Century Duck Crisis Special
added.description: The park guys want to get rid of a very large bird in the park.

added.title: A Bunch of Full Grown Geese
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to get rid of some geese that are causing problems at the park.

added.title: My Mom
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby are forced to work under Muscle Man and endure his repetitive jokes.

added.title: A Bunch of Baby Ducks
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby come across a family of ducks living in a fountain at the park and take quite a shine to them.

added.title: The Power
added.description: Mordecai & Rigby find a mysterious keyboard that allows them to do anything they want, including accidently sending Benson to the moon.

added.title: Just Set Up the Chairs
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby get distracted while setting up chairs for a kids birthday party and unleash a monster that terrorizes the entire park.

added.title: Caffeinated Concert Tickets
added.description: Mordecai & Rigby make a deal with a Coffee Bean to help them stay awake to work major overtime to pay for concert tickets.

added.title: Death Punchies
added.description: Rigby learns an ultimate karate move and becomes the bully of the park.

added.title: Free Cake
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby throw Skips a surprise birthday party in order to get free cake.

added.title: Meat Your Maker
added.description: After Rigby causes the guys to get locked in a meat locker, he must get help from some hot dogs in order to get them out.

added.title: Grilled Cheese Deluxe
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby lie about being astronauts in order to cut in line at a restaurant.

added.title: The Unicorns Have Got to Go
added.description: In order to impress Margret and ask her out, Mordecai hangs with a bunch of punk Unicorns who say they can help him get his lady.

added.title: Prank Callers
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby try and prank the Master Prank Caller to be the best prank callers. The MPC sends them back to 1982.

added.title: Don
added.description: Rigby's estranged accountant brother comes back to help save the park from an audit. While everyone loves Don, Rigby wants nothing to do with him.

added.title: Coming Soon
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby find a voice modulator that makes them sound like a movie preview voiceover guy.

added.title: Pizza Pouch Drop
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby risk their lives to cook pizza pouches evenly on all sides.

added.title: The 1973 Tetherball Championship Trophy
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby compete to win a vintage tetherball championship trophy.

added.title: Ninja Shoes
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby try to sneak out of the house wearing ninja shoes.

added.title: Synth Buttons
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby realize that the bridge of the ship is also a synthesizer.

added.title: Robot Rap Battle
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have a rap battle with robots.

added.title: 2001: A Nap Odyssey
added.description: The guys take a nap in zero gravity.

added.title: Time Loop
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby get stuck in a space-time loop.

added.title: Space Worm
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby ride a needy space worm.

added.title: Break Time
added.description: Benson breakdances during a work break.

added.title: Fun Run
added.description: Pops goes on a fun run across the country.

added.title: Pilot
added.description: When two best friends, a blue jay named Mordecai and a raccoon named Rigby, play a game of rock, paper, scissors over a couch, it leads to dangerous results.

added.title: Powerprof.
added.description: The girls are so busy fighting crime that the Professor doesn't get to see them anymore. So he creates a superhero suit for himself. Unfortunately, he starts cramping their superhero style.

added.title: The Headsucker's Moxy/Equal Fights
added.description: The Headsucker's Moxy: There's a mysterious villain in town who's sucking pertinent information from the brains of powerful people and committing crimes. How do the girls trap this sucker before his next victim is drained?/Equal Fights: When the girls try to catch a local female villain, she tells them that as women they've got to stick together. It's up to the women of Townsville to teach our heroines the true meaning of equality.

added.title: Three Girls and a Monster/Monkey See, Doggy Two
added.description: Three Girls and a Monster: The girls are once again in a furious battle with a ferocious monster. But Blossom and Buttercup can't agree on how to fight the beast and Bubbles just wants everyone to get along./Monkey See, Doggy Two: Mojo has discovered a fatal flaw in his brilliant plan and decides to reenact it step-by-step. The girls think they're experiencing deja vu but it's really just Mojo working his maniacal mischief.

added.title: Jewel of the Aisle/Super Zeroes
added.description: Jewel of the Isle: A crook hides a huge diamond in a box of the girls' favorite cereal. But how can he trick the girls into giving him some cereal in order to get the jewel back?/Super Zeroes: The girls don't think they have enough superhero accessories like those found in the comic books. They begin to emulate their favorite characters, complete with gadgets and gizmos.

added.title: Moral Decay/Meet the Beat Alls
added.description: Moral Decay: When Bubbles loses a tooth, she gets a shiny coin under her pillow the next day. Buttercup sees a gold mine in the mouths of Townsville's criminal element./Meet the Beat Alls: Mojo, Him, Princess and Fuzzy band together to form the Bad Four, a criminal supergroup out to destroy the Powerpuff Girls. Everything is going great until Mojo meets Moko Jono and falls in love.

added.title: Gettin' Twiggy with It/Cop Out
added.description: Getting' Twiggy with It: Mitch takes Twiggy, the class hamster, home for the weekend. But when Mitch flushes Twiggy down the toilet, he emerges bigger and badder than ever./Cop Out: A lazy Townsville cop gets fired and blames the girls for saving the day too often, thereby stealing his job. Now, it's payback time and he has the perfect plan to stop those pint-size punks.

added.title: Hot Air Buffoon/Ploys R' Us
added.description: Hot Air Buffoon: The Mayor realizes the girls are doing all the work in his city for him. So he mans a hot air balloon and starts fighting crime the old-fashioned way./Ploys R' Us: The girls wake up to find their room filled with toys. They soon figure out that the Professor has been sleepwalking and stealing. Instead of reporting it, the girls take advantage of the situation.

added.title: Cat Man Do/Impeach Fuzz
added.description: Cat Man Do: Bubbles saves a seemingly innocent kitty from the clutches of an evil villain. But when the girls discover it's actually the Cat who is evil, they must save the Professor from being the next victim./Impeach Fuzz: When Fuzzy Lumkins throws his hat into the mayoral ring and claims a surprise victory, it's up to the Mayor and the girls to wrestle the office, and the Mayor's actual hat, back from him.

added.title: Power Up Puff
added.description: During a fight, both Buttercup and Bubbles are surprised to discover they've leveled up, leaving Blossom to wonder when or if she'll get new powers too.

added.title: Spoooooky Game
added.description: The gang's weekly board game night has been getting a little too competitive lately, so when Unikitty finds a spooky old board game that's clearly haunted, their desire to win gets turned upside down, but cursed or not, they'll be the first to the finish line!

added.title: Sparkle Matter Matters
added.description: Unikitty learns that boring, old Richard has never produced any happy Sparkle Matter ever, she cooks up a formula with Dr. Fox that will overload him with emotions! Now, he's making so much Sparkle Matter it's threatening to destroy the kingdom! Can Unikitty help Richard find emotional balance before all is lost?

added.title: No Day Like Snow Day
added.description: When a blizzard hits the town, Master Frown tries to ruin everyone's fun by pretending to be a magical snowman! But when he gets frozen inside, Master Frown must worry less about ruining everyone's good time and instead not turning into a Frown-sicle, while he's forced to experience the joys of the holiday season!

added.title: Action Forest
added.description: Hawkodile is the toughest action hero in the land, until his old rival shows up to take vengeance on him. Defeated and in need of help, Hawkodile must train Unikitty and the others into super muscle­y tough bros. And there's only one place unstoppable warriors are made, the Action Forest.

added.title: Kaiju Kitty
added.description: When a giant monster attacks the Unikingdom, the gang fights back with Dr. Fox's awesome new secret weapon: a massive mega robot! But after the threat is contained, Unikitty doesn't want to stop using the  awesome robot, so she finds excuses for them to use it for everything, no matter how pointless. But what if the greatest threat to the kingdom turns out to be them?

added.title: Fire & Nice
added.description: When Master Frown causes Unikitty to have an angry outburst that gets a little too destructive, she wishes her Rage Kitty side wasn't part of her anymore. Thanks to a new Dr. Fox invention, she gets her wish: Rage Kitty and Nice Unikitty split apart into two! But with Unikitty now unable to get angry, she learns bottling up your anger is never a good thing.

added.title: Rock Friend
added.description: Unikitty discovers Puppycorn's only other friend is a boring old rock. Encouraged to "make more friends," Puppycorn just can't find someone he clicks with, until he takes her advice and decides to literally make a new friend out of the best parts of his friends. This won't go well.

added.title: Kitchen Chaos
added.description: After a workplace injury, Richard is unable to do his servant work. Unikitty and the others take on the task of one simple chore, clean the kitchen. This incredibly boring task taxes our heroes as they find every way possible to not do it. Will they be able to accomplish this goal and bring Richard back?

added.title: Crushing Defeat
added.description: When Hawkodile develops a secret crush on Dr. Fox, he finds himself actually crushing down in size! With Hawkodile too embarrassed to tell her (or anyone) about it, Unikitty and the gang become his love gurus to help him confess his feelings before he shrinks away into nothing!

added.title: Wishing Well
added.description: When Puppycorn uses a wishing well and it doesn't come true, Unikitty is shocked to discover the reason: all the wishes made over the years can't be granted because they're trapped at the bottom of the well (it's a dumb system.) She frees them to bring joy to the town… only to discover that they've gone a little bad after years trapped in a dark hole. Soon, they wish it would end!

added.title: Hide N' Seek
added.description: Unikitty is proud to be the reigning champ of Hide N' Seek Day. But when Unikitty finds everyone in the kingdom except for Richard, she hunts him down at all costs. Will Richard continue to elude the Princess at her favorite game, and if so, how?!

added.title: Stuck Together
added.description: When Master Frown's head is stuck on Unikitty's butt, she vows to help him get his own body back, but first, she has to attend to her nice princess duties! But sharing a body with Master Frown can get pretty complicated, especially when Master Frown has his own agenda.

added.title: Little Prince Puppycorn
added.description: Puppycorn finally realizes he's a prince, so he wants to be in charge of the kingdom for once! Despite their friends' concerns, Unikitty makes Puppycorn ruler but realizes absolute power in the hands of the pup is too much for him to handle and his ideas aren't exactly great. Can they remove him from power while keeping the kingdom from revolting?

added.title: Pet Pet
added.description: Unikitty and the gang bring home a tiny creature they name Pet Pet, but Richard won't let them keep it if they can't prove they are responsible owners. But when Pet Pet runs away, Unikitty must pretend to be Pet Pet until they can find him, or Richard will never let them have Pet Pet (or any pet) ever again! Will Unikitty survive pet training, or finally admit responsibility is a lot harder than she thought?

added.title: Kitty Court
added.description: When Unikitty has a little auto incident with Master Frown, he insists on taking it to court! Frown's thrilled. There's nothing worse than boring old court and he can't wait to subject Unikitty to it! Unikitty is happy to make things right but the trial will be in Unikitty Court, which is so nonsensical and fun. It's Frown's worst nightmare! Will Master Frown succeed in bumming Unikitty out? Or will he be the one punished by their legal antics?

added.title: Motel
added.description: Following an insect mishap Clarence's house needs to be fumigated forcing Mary, Chad, and Clarence into a motel. In the meantime, Clarence and Chad learn a bit about responsibility while Mary contemplates a life of letting go.

added.title: Rock Show
added.description: Chad's band Dogmon, plays a show for the first time in years, giving Clarence and Mary a chance to really rock out.

added.title: Karate Mom
added.description: After surprising Clarence with Martial Arts classes at the "Aberdojo," Mary gets talked into joining the class herself. She loves the slow-paced lessons in discipline and control, but Clarence just wants to have fun and kick butt! Can Mary convince Clarence to stick with the class, earn his belt and have some fun with her?

added.title: Dinner Party
added.description: When Clarence's mom takes Clarence to a stuffy dinner party, Clarence embarks on a quest for fun wherever it can be found.

added.title: Hurricane Dilliss
added.description: Things in the Wendle household are turned upside down when Mary's mom Dyllis comes to visit, butting her way into every corner of Clarence, Mary and Chad's life.

added.title: Numbskull
added.description: A head Injury turns Mr. Gus into a bumbling fools whose wacky antics make him Uncle Grandpa's coolest friend. No longer the focus of Uncle Grandpa's attention, a jealous Pizza Steve tries to desperately to get back normal. Mr. Gus has to restore social balance in the RV.

added.title: Shower Party
added.description: Things get out of hand when Andrew W. K. helps Pizza Steve and Mr. Gus throw a party while Uncle Grandpa is in the shower.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Land
added.description: Pizza Steve must find a way to sneak onto his own roller coaster at the newly opened Uncle Grandpa Land.

added.title: Taco Comet
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang go undercover to taste the most sought after treat in the cosmos: the Taco Comet.

added.title: The Fan
added.description: Uncle Grandpa's number one fan gets more than he bargained for when Uncle Grandpa overstays his welcome.

added.title: The Package
added.description: The gang gets nutty after repeatedly failing to open a mysterious package.

added.title: Are You Talking to Tree?
added.description: When the tree inside the RV begins talking to Uncle Grandpa, he must convince the gang that he's not going crazy.

added.title: Older
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa mistakenly transforms a young boy into a three-hundred-year-old man, he must manage to turn the kid back to normal before anyone gets hurt.

added.title: Guest Directed Shorts
added.description: A showcase of three Uncle Grandpa shorts presented in three unique animation styles.

added.title: Hundred Dollar Gus
added.description: Pizza Steve makes up a preposterous lie that lands the gang in big trouble.

added.title: Weird Badge
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a young girl learn unconventional survival skills that help rescue her endangered camping troop.

added.title: The Great Spaghetti Western
added.description: Mr. Gus repeatedly runs afoul of a crooked mayor while winning the hears of the townsfolk.

added.title: Pal.0
added.description: When the RV's talking computer system malfunctions, Uncle Grandpa and the gang must figure out a way to stop the rogue computer and restore life in the RV back to normal.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa at the Movies
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve cause a ruckus at the movies, Mr. Gus is forced to play the hero in order to save the day.

added.title: Tiger and Mouse
added.description: An unlikely friendship between Giant Realistic Flying Tiger and a mouse threatens to destroy everything inside the RV.

added.title: The Dark Night
added.description: Much to everyone's surprise, Bam is secretly afraid of the dark. When Poison Ivy knocks out all the power in Gotham, Bam must conquer his fears to stop her.

added.title: License to Joke
added.description: When Redbird tries his hand at espionage as "V-8, the Super-Spy", he quickly realizes he's gotten in over his head, so Redbird teams up with Bibi to save the Amusement Mile from Dr. Spy!

added.title: Bibi's Bad Day
added.description: Bibi has a terrible no-good day after she keeps messing up and lets Joker get away. She doesn't think he can help Batgirl anymore, but a "bad today" doesn't mean it'll be a "bad tomorrow."

added.title: A Jet Out of Water
added.description: After refusing to practice with her new underwater mode, Batwing is unable to save Batman from Penguin's sunken ship trap. The Batwheels must help Wing practice her submersible skills before she can save the day.

added.title: Batty Body Swap
added.description: After agreeing to swap motherboards and change bodies, the Batwheels have to quickly learn to "drive a mile in each other's wheels" in time to stop the approaching Legion of Zoom!

added.title: Outer Space
added.description: The Looney Builders build Marvin the Martian and his Martian crew a space station. Marvin soon becomes overwhelmed by his Martian crew's antics and lack of personal space.

added.title: Catwalk
added.description: The Looney Builders are hired by Penelope Pussycat to build a fashion runway in France where they are encouraged to make their design bigger and more fun.

added.title: Dim Sum
added.description: Chef Poyung Panda hires The Looney Builders to build her a Dim Sum bus in China. The crew faces a major setback and Bugs worries about letting down his favorite chef.

added.title: Crane Game
added.description: As The Looney Builders build a giant claw game for Chibi Critter's arcade in Japan, they discover the claw part is broken.

added.title: Speedy
added.description: The Looney Builders rush to build a soccer stadium in Mexico for their fast customer, Speedy Gonzalez.

added.title: Family Photo
added.description: When the family has to dress up for a family photo, Jessica decides to express herself.

added.title: Drawing Time
added.description: When the tv goes out, Jessica and her friends make up their own story to entertain themselves.

added.title: Percy in the Middle
added.description: After Gordon tells all the young engines that they have a day off to relax, Thomas and Diesel insist on a teamed relay race through the obstacle course. Percy is the only one who isn't interested in playing, so Thomas asks him to referee instead. He reluctantly agrees and the race is on! Coming to a split second finish, Percy determines Thomas' team wins, but Diesel doesn't accept and calls for a rematch. Once again the teams race and Diesel wins after accidentally causing an oil spill. Both teams become so angry with each other, they're too distracted when Percy runs off to chase butterflies. Thomas, Diesel, and friends finally notice Percy's absence and speed after him, but they'll need to learn their lesson about sportsmanship if they want to ensure this day off is a success.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Bad Luck Boxcar
added.description: When Thomas and Percy must transport an unlucky boxcar of bananas, Thomas seems to have bad luck. Percy's positive attitude helps Thomas see the luck in each scenario, breaking the myth of the curse for a successful delivery.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Not So Easy-Greasy
added.description: Nia is nervous about working with Tess, the fastest -- and bossiest -- crane on Sodor! When Nia's plan for a safe and speedy delivery goes awry and causes Tess' wheels to clog with sand, they recruit handy Sandy to solve their problem. Luckily, Sandy has a new invention to get Tess up and going again: a tanker full of her Super-Slick Easy-Greasy Crane Grease! However, chaos continues to ensue when Nia gets stuck in the mud and the runaway grease spills all over Sodor! In the midst of the madness, Nia learns how to fix her original plan and save Sodor from slipping and sliding!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: It All Adds Up
added.description: It is a special day for Harold -- the Northern Lights will shimmer over Sodor at sunset! He cannot wait to share this moment with his engine friends on Lookout Mountain. However, Thomas and the gang have a busy day ahead of them, which is impacted by damage to the Sodor Suspension Bridge. Carly and Sandy warn the excited engines that they should only cross the bridge in case of an emergency -- a rule that is ignored by Kana, Diesel, Nia, AND Thomas! When the bridge finally collapses and prevents them from reaching Lookout Mountain in time, Harold selflessly chooses to help his friends instead of see the Lights. His sacrifice teaches the young engines an important lesson: your actions add up - stay away until it is safe to play.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Bruno's Map Mishap
added.description: Bruno is beyond delighted -- he has received the gift of an updated map of Sodor from Sir Topham Hatt! He and Thomas can't wait to use it to navigate their busy schedule for the day. But when Kana's speedy whoosh blows Bruno's beloved map up, up, and away, Thomas and Bruno team up with Percy and Diesel to recover it! While searching the island far and wide for Bruno's prized possession, the gang discovers that there is something more important than keeping their schedules -- their friendship!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Seeking a Safer Sodor
added.description: After a near-collision rattles their wheels, Percy and Kana enlist the help of Emily to introduce new safety measures all over Sodor. However, their anxiousness about accidents push Percy and Kana to ridiculous extremes that only makes more trouble! When Percy has another accident caused by his off-the-rails safety obsession, he refuses to leave Tidmouth Sheds. When he has to leap into action to help his friends, Percy learns that paying attention to your surroundings is the best way to not have an accident.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: A Cranky Goodbye
added.description: When Bulstrode excitedly announces that he is getting a brand new paint job on the Mainland, everyone is thrilled for him -- except for a crankier-than-usual Cranky. When the crane's dismissive comments upset Bulstrode, the tugboat storms off, leaving Thomas and Percy to pick up the pieces, repair their friendship, and encourage both of them to do something they have never done before -- talk about their true feelings towards each other!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Sameroo
added.description: Gordon has a day-long assignment for Thomas and the Troublesome Trucks -- they have to transport delivery after delivery to Vicarstown! The Troublesome Trucks are less than enthused -- this "sameroo" job will bore them out of their bolts! The Number One Engine is determined to make the day "amazeroo" for them and does his best to turn their repeated route into a new adventure! After their game of "Switcheroo" gets them lost, Thomas and the Troublesome Trucks learn that routine is not necessarily a bad thing -- in fact, it can be very helpful!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Thomas for a Day
added.description: It's a blustery day on Sodor and Percy finds that his preferred route is closed! He must journey into Crumble Canyon -- a place that makes him terribly nervous! But before he can face his fears, Diesel blasts by, bonking his cargo of blue paint all over the jittery mail engine! Percy is unrecognizable as himself -- instead, he looks just like Thomas! His impromptu makeover inspires Percy to be brave just like his best loco-migo -- and pretend to be the Number One Engine for the day! When Whiff loses his glasses, Percy escorts him across the island and learns that the bravery isn't in the blue paint -- it's inside him!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: The Super Axle
added.description: Sodor welcomes a new engine to the group -- Toby the Tram Engine! Thomas, Diesel, Kana, and the other loco-migos are eager to include their new friend in their deliveries and assigned duties. But as he shadows them, their jobs prove to be a bit too intense for the older engine -- in fact, Toby glumly starts to believe maybe he is too old. Determined to pick up Toby's spirits, Thomas and Sandy get creative and turn an old axle into a "superaxleatortron" -- a 'brand-new' part to put the pep back in Toby's confidence! When the plan goes sideways because the other engines want "super-axles" too, Toby discovers that he never needed the special part -- he just needed to believe in himself!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: The Waiting Game
added.description: Bruno and Nia are tasked with teaming up to help someone very special to the savvy brake car -- a mechanic! But when Bulstrode and his wrench shipment are delayed, it sends Bruno into an agitated tail-spin. To soothe their friend, the engines decide to pass the time by playing the ultimate Waiting Game and learning how to have fun while daydreaming, anticipating, and practicing patience!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: L-L-Lellogames
added.description: Mei has set up an obstacle course for Ella and friends that turns farmyard chores into a fun game!

added.title: Halloween Dress Up
added.description: It's Halloween and there's a monster, a skeleton, a vampire, a dinosaur and a pirate on the farm!

added.title: Jelly Jam Jam
added.description: Ella helps Mei make some delicious jams using fresh produce from Lellobee City Farm.

added.title: Old Macdonald
added.description: Ella and Bee play a game of hide and seek on the farm with Carlos, Pablo, Lettie and Heidi.

added.title: Wake Up Dance
added.description: It's nearly dawn on the farm and a scarecrow called Sunny joins Ella to wake up the animals.

added.title: Taz in Toyland/Born to Sing (song)/A Secret Tweet
added.description: Taz in Toyland: After Taz breaks all of his toys, Granny gives him one last chance to care for something./A Secret Tweet: The babies plan a surprise birthday party for Tweety.

added.title: Comfort Level/Twinkle Baby Looney Star (song)/Like a Duck to Water
added.description: Comfort Level: Sylvester learns to live without his blankey./Like a Duck to Water: Daffy overcomes his fear of the swimming pool.

added.title: School Daze/Mary Had a Baby Duck (song)/Things That Go Bugs in the Night
added.description: School Daze: The babies play pretend school in preparation for the real thing./Things That Go Bugs in the Night: Bugs must find the courage to discover what's making scary noises outside.

added.title: The Creature from the Chocolate Chip/The Looney Riddle (song)/Card Bored Box
added.description: Creature from the Chocolate Chip: Sylvester eats all of Granny's cookies then makes up a cookie monster to blame./Card Bored Box: Faced with nothing to do, the babies use a cardboard box and their imaginations to make playtime fun.

added.title: Time and Time Again/Does Your Tongue Hang Low (song)/May the Best Taz Win
added.description: Time and Time Again: The babies learn the importance of telling time./May the Best Taz Win: Lola learns she can't be the best at every sport.

added.title: Mine!/Over the Burrow (song)/Sylvester the Pester
added.description: Mine!: Daffy learns a lesson in doing the right thing when he finds a purse filled with money./Sylvester the Pester: An attention-starved Sylvester won't let Granny have any time to herself.

added.title: Cat-Taz-Trophy/If You're Looney (song)/Duck! Monster! Duck!
added.description: Cat-Taz-Trophy: Sylvester and Taz team up to win a toy racecar derby./Duck! Monster! Duck!: Daffy reads the babies a scary story, only to end up frightening himself.

added.title: The Brave Little Tweety/Foghorn's Talkin' in the Barnyard (song)/Puddle Olympics
added.description: The Brave Little Tweety: Tweety takes a role in a play too seriously and begins to believe he's a real superhero./The Puddle Olympics: The kids take turns jumping over a puddle but Sylvester is afraid of the water.

added.title: A Lot Like Lola/Baby Elmer Had a Friend (song)/Mother's Day Madness
added.description: A Lot Like Lola: Lola wants everyone to be more like her until they all start acting exactly like her./Mother's Day Madness: The babies compete to see who can create the best Mother's Day card.

added.title: Takers Keepers/D-A-F-F-Y (song)/To Tell the Tooth
added.description: Takers Keepers: Daffy steals Taz's favorite toy but he learns you can't just take everything you want./To Tell the Tooth: When Bugs loses a baby tooth, Daffy tries to figure out how to scam the tooth fairy.

added.title: Spin Out/Taz's Fridge (song)/Snow Day
added.description: Spinout: Taz learns a tough lesson. He shouldn't spin after eating too much candy./Snow Day: The babies experience their first snowfall.

added.title: Shadow of a Doubt/John Jacob Jongle Elmer Fudd (song)/Christmas in July
added.description: Shadow of a Doubt: Tweety sheds some light on what a shadow is./Christmas in July: The babies pretend it's Christmas in hopes of getting Lola the stethoscope she wants.

added.title: Bruce Bunny/Baby Bunny (song)/Leader of the Pack
added.description: Bruce Bunny: When Daffy starts making up hurtful rhymes, Bugs changes his name to Bruce./Leader of the Pack: Daffy starts a secret password club for everyone except Bugs.

added.title: Flower Power/Looney Tunes Zoo (song)/Lightning Bugs Sylvester
added.description: Flower Power: The babies all want to pick the best flowers for Granny but they end up destroying her garden./Lightning Bugs Sylvester: Sylvester learns to overcome his fear of lightning.

added.title: Flush Hour/Paws and Feathers (song)/I Strain
added.description: Flush Hour: The babies learn the purpose of toilets./I Strain: Petunia gets hooked on watching television and stops playing with her friends.

added.title: The Sandman Is Coming/Ten Loonies in a Bed (song)/Some Assembly Required
added.description: The Sandman Is Coming: Daffy thinks the Sandman is a monster that throws sand in children's eyes./Some Assembly Required: Bugs gets a new toy with assembly required and has to learn to follow instructions.

added.title: All Washed Up/My Bunny Lies Over the Ocean (song)/Did Not! Did Too!
added.description: All Washed Up: Taz decides he doesn't like taking a bath./Did Not! Did Too!: Bugs and Lola temporarily decide that they don't want to be friends any longer.

added.title: Tea & Basketball/Down by the Cage (song)/Taz You Like It
added.description: Tea & Basketball: Sylvester wants to play tea with the girls while Lola wants to play basketball with the boys./Taz You Like It: Taz discovers pratfalls get him laughs and attention.

added.title: Band Together/Oh Where, Oh Where Has My Baby Martian Gone (song)/War of the Weirds
added.description: Band Together: The babies learn about music and improvise their own orchestra./War of the Weirds: Marvin the Martian comes to visit, and the babies learn to accept differences.

added.title: The Harder They Fall/The Hare Hid Under the Fountain (song)/Business as Unusual
added.description: The Harder They Fall: Bugs is embarrassed to admit he doesn't know how to skate./Business as Unusual: Bugs and Daffy open competing lemonade stands.

added.title: Mr. McStuffles/Twinkle, Baby Looney Star (song)/Picture This!
added.description: Mr. McStuffles: Daffy doesn't want to give up his old toy, even after he's outgrown it./Picture This: The babies create their own endings to fairytales.

added.title: Hair Cut-Ups/Does Your Tongue Hang Low (song)/A Clean Sweep
added.description: Hair Cut-Ups: Lola is afraid of getting her first haircut./A Clean Sweep: Daffy tries to avoid cleaning up by sweeping his toys under a rug.

added.title: Daffy Did It!/Foghorn's Talkin' in the Barnyard (song)/Pig Who Cried Woof
added.description: Daffy Did It!: Tweety blames Daffy for his mistake, and then has trouble living with the guilt of lying./The Pig Who Cried Wolf: Petunia fakes emergencies. But when a real one arises, no one believes her.

added.title: New Cat in Town/Baby Bunny (song)/The Magic of Spring
added.description: New Cat in Town: Sylvester is jealous of the attention baby Pepe is receiving./The Magic of Spring: Bugs' failure as a magician turns to success when he experiences the true magic of nature.

added.title: For Whom the Toll Calls/John Jacob Jongle Elmer Fudd (song)/Cereal Boxing
added.description: For Whom the Toll Calls: Petunia and Tweety learn how to call long distance and amass a huge phone bill./Cereal Boxing: The kids become obsessed with getting the prizes from boxes of sugary cereal.

added.title: Who Said That?/Paws and Feathers (song)/Let Them Make Cake
added.description: Who Said That?: Daffy learns a bad word and must learn not to use it./Let Them Make Cake: Melissa wants cake, but she wants the other babies to bake it for her.

added.title: Mind Your Manners/Down by the Cage (song)/Petunia the Piggy Bank
added.description: Mind Your Manners: The babies learn proper dinner etiquette when preparing to dine out with Granny./Petunia the Piggy Bank: The kids start getting an allowance but only Petunia thinks to save for something special.

added.title: A Pastime for Petunia/Looney Tunes Zoo (song)/Pouting Match
added.description: A Pastime for Petunia: Petunia has a difficult time finding a hobby that doesn't imitate the other babies' interests./Pouting Match: Lola tries pouting to get what she wants, and soon all the babies are doing it.

added.title: Wise Quacker/D-A-F-F-Y (song)/Yours, Mine...and Mine, Mine!
added.description: Wise Quacker: Bugs gets laughs doing hurtful impressions of the other kids, but he takes the jokes too far./Yours, Mine...and Mine Mine Mine!: Daffy thinks if he shares his old toys, Granny will buy him all new toys.

added.title: Loose Change/Oh Where, Oh Where Has My Baby Martian Gone (song)/Act Your Age
added.description: Loose Change: Sylvester is upset when Granny paints the bedroom but he learns the importance of change./Act Your Age: The kids try to see who can act most like a baby, while vying for Granny's attention.

added.title: Who's Your Granny?/If You're Looney (song)/The Tattletale
added.description: Who's Your Granny?: When Granny gets sick, Lola tries to take over her responsibilities./The Tattletale: Lola begins tattling on the other babies until her friends no longer want to play with her.

added.title: The Yolk's on You/Baby Elmer Had a Friend (song)/Baby-Gate
added.description: The Yolk's on You: Daffy and Melissa team up to play jokes on the other babies./Baby Gate: Melissa spreads rumors about the babies, and Bugs goes undercover to find the truth.

added.title: Never Say Try/Taz's Fridge (song)/Pair O' Dice Lost
added.description: Never Say Try: Sylvester is a bad dancer and finger painter so he believes he'll never be good at anything./Pair O' Dice Lost: Daffy feels defeated whenever things aren't going his way.

added.title: Melissa the Hero/My Bunny Lies over the Ocean (song)/The Trouble with Larry
added.description: Melissa the Hero: Melissa brags about helping Petunia to the point of self-aggrandizement./The Trouble with Larry: Petunia invents an imaginary friend to help her always get her way.

added.title: The Littlest Tweety/Over the Burrow (song)/In Bugs We Trust
added.description: The Littlest Tweety: Tweety is tired of being overlooked because of his diminutive size./In Bugs We Trust: Bugs uses the babies' money to buy different toys than he promised.

added.title: Cool for Cats/Ten Loonies in a Bed (song)/Time Out!
added.description: Cool for Cats: Sylvester believes a commercial that says eating Chewy Chomps will make him cool./Time Out!: Bugs, Daffy and Taz are disciplined by having a time out in the corner.

added.title: Present Tense/The Hare Hid Under the Fountain (song)/The Neat and the Sloppy
added.description: Present Tense: The Baby Looney Tunes pitch in to make an Arbor Day gift for Granny while Baby Lola, who suggested they do so, tries to make Granny a present on her own./The Neat and the Sloppy: A study in contrasts enlivens this odd couple's antics. Baby Daffy is the compulsive mess maker, and Baby Sylvester is the cleanliness freak.

added.title: Tell-A-Photo/Born to Sing (song)/Move It!
added.description: Tell-A-Photo: As Granny assembles her photo album, the babies gather around to reminisce about all the happy times they've spent together./Move It!: Overhearing Granny making a call to Manny the Mover, Baby Bugs and Baby Lola jump to the conclusion they're all moving away from Granny's house.

added.title: Nightbike
added.description: Bibi has some competition with Nightwing's motorcycle, Nightbike. Always trying to one-up each other, these stunt bikes will need to learn that they're better when they work together.

added.title: Bat-Light Blow-Out
added.description: When Ducky and Quizz steal the Bat-Signal's one-of-a-kind lightbulb, Bam and Batwing must find a way to restore the legendary light so Batman knows when Gotham needs him.

added.title: Kitty's Sleepover
added.description: Kitty is staying over at the Batcave for a sleepover, but getting her to lie down for a catnap is no easy task as the Batwheels have to find creative ways to get her to sleep.

added.title: Mission: Stuffed Animal
added.description: When Redbird takes one of Buff's stuffed animals without asking and it accidentally gets swiped by the Legion of Zoom, Red enlists Bam to help him make a daring rescue.

added.title: Follow the Bouncing Bam
added.description: When Bam is covered in super bouncy Bounce X goo during a chase with Prank, he must learn to embrace and use his newfound bouncing abilities to his advantage if he's going to put a stop to Prank's latest scheme.

added.title: Ace in the Hole
added.description: When a group of alley dogs, aided by a heroic stray, are saved from Catwoman by kind-hearted Buff, he brings them all back to live in the Batcave, unbeknownst to the rest of the Bat-Family.

added.title: Mechanic Panic
added.description: When Jestah injures herself preparing for an extreme sports competition with the other Zoomers, Bibi helps her overcome her fear of going to the mechanic so she can heal up in time to compete.

added.title: Improvise My Ride
added.description: When Buff's trusty winch is knocked out of action by Poison Ivy, he must learn to improvise and come up with creative solutions on the fly.

added.title: Dynamic Du-Oh-No
added.description: When Snowy and Jestah team up to execute a mysterious plan involving rare freeze-berries, Batwing and Buff pair up to take on the dastardly duo, but Batwing decides to carry out the mission herself, putting both her and Buff at risk.

added.title: To the Batmobile!
added.description: When all of the Batwheels (except for Bam) mysteriously disappear, Bam enlists the help of A.D.A.M, the original Batmobile, to help save his friends. Along the way, Bam comes to appreciate the old-school mobile's different crimefighting style as they team up to take on the Legion of Zoom.

added.title: The Easter Bunnies
added.description: The Easter Bunny is sick, so she hires The Looney Builders to take over the festivities and ensure Looneyburg has a great Easter.

added.title: Junior
added.description: The Looney Builders are hired by Ma and Pa Bear to build a bedroom for their son, Junior, whose excitement causes setbacks.

added.title: Looney Moon
